From: Giovanni Gherdovich <ggherdovich@suse.cz>
Subject: dbs_data kABI workaround
Patch-mainline: Never, kABI workaround
References: bsc#1237800 CVE-2022-49513

Add a trailing member to dbs_data. The structure is allocated and
managed by the cpufreq core, not the modules using it. This means the
argument against enlarging it at the end (existing modules may copy it
using its old size, truncating the last member) doesn't apply.

Furthermore, this struct is for cpufreq governors, and is very
unlikely any partner is making an out-of-tree governor module.

Signed-off-by: Giovanni Gherdovich <ggherdovich@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/cpufreq/cpufreq_governor.h |    2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/cpufreq/cpufreq_governor.h
+++ b/drivers/cpufreq/cpufreq_governor.h
@@ -43,7 +43,9 @@ struct dbs_data {
 	unsigned int sampling_down_factor;
 	unsigned int up_threshold;
 	unsigned int io_is_busy;
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
 	struct dbs_governor *gov;
+#endif
 };
 
 static inline struct dbs_data *to_dbs_data(struct gov_attr_set *attr_set)
